commitResults.messageTitle: Initial commit because I forgot to commit the Level-1 in the previous version, and I followed some guide on StackOverFlow to rebase - and then i encountered some errors.
Level-0: Initial commit that simply greets the user and exits.
Level-1: Improve the skeletal version of Duke so that it echos commands entered by the user, and exits when the user types the command bye.
Level-2: Add the ability to store whatever text entered by the user and display them back to the user when requested.

Level-3: changed the switch-case construct to if-else, and added a new Task class that was lifted off course site. Add the ability to mark tasks as done and the ability to change the status back to not done.
Level-4: Add support for tracking three types of tasks: ToDos, Events, Deadlines. Changed all the variables in each class to be a private variable. No error handling yet.
A-TextUiTesting: Use the input/output redirection technique to semi-automate the testing of Duke.
commitResults.messageBody: Removed trailing whitespace in welcome message.

commitResults.messageTitle: Level-4_interim: Shifted Task/Todo/Event/Deadline into its own folder to make it neater.
Level-5_interim: Separated the logic for the Parser, Exceptions, and grouped all tasks types in a single package.
Level-5_interim: Changed error message to be more descriptive; specifically for the todo, deadline, positive integer.
commitResults.messageBody:
Handles un/mark a, un/mark -2, un/mark 100 (number beyond the current tasks created etc).

Trim user input to prevent user from entering a empty item in the command String for all 3 types.

commitResults.messageTitle: Level-5: Enabled error handling.
Level-6_interim: satisfied baseline handling for the delete case.
Level-6_interim: added enums
Level-6 and A-TextUiTesting: Broke apart commands (DELETE/MARK/UNMARK) that have an index component to them using an enum.
Added file storage to HDD support...
Do not allow user to access Tasks that has not been created yet.
Slightly changed error message.
Level-7_interim: allow printing so that file can be properly stored in the database.
Default the task when added is considered incomplete
Level-7_interim: placeholder function to write value to database is now working.
Level-7_interim: added a sample save method
Level-7_interim: Allow data to be rebuilt once the app is re-opened. Rebuild database once data is modified.
Level-7_interim: Added database txt file.
Merge branch 'branch-Level-7'
